title: Cranberry Ginger Chutney
description:
There's more than one way to sauce a cranberry. We prove it over and over again each holiday season, when our 
cache of cranberry condiments arrives on our shelves and in our refrigerators. We have options that can cater 
to anyone's cranberry cravings, and this year, we've added yet another standout to the cranberry condiment 
crowd: Trader Joe's Cranberry Ginger Chutney. 

Inspired by the aromatic flavors of South Indian cuisine, Trader Joe's Cranberry Ginger Chutney invites a 
welcome touch of global inspiration to your Thanksgiving table. Our supplier starts by boiling whole cranberries, 
but only lightly, so as to maintain a chunky texture. Next, they sweeten them with sugar and combine them 
with ginger, garlic, and cayenne pepper, resulting in a sweet and savory profile that plays well with the tangy, 
tart fruitiness of the cranberries. Enjoy this Chutney with your turkey dinner, give it a supporting role on your 
next charcuterie board, or use it as spread for crackers, sanwiches, wraps, and more!

Cranberry Ginger Chutney

title: White Queso Dip
description:
Guacamole, salsa, and queso dip are the holy trinity of scoopable Mexican restaurant appetizers. Peruse the 
refrigerators at your neighborhood Trader Joe's, and you'll notice we're two for three on this front, with a 
plethora of guacamole and salsa options to choose from. With the debut of Trader Joe's White Queso Dip, 
we're finally three for three!

Our Queso starts with tangy white cheddar-it comprises 50% of the recipe, in fact! We mix in cream for extra 
richness, plus sea salt and onion for savory aromatics. Mild red & green bell peppers add a touch of sweetness 
(and festive red & green speckles throughout), while diced jalapeños lend a just-right amount of heat. Go 
ahead, shovel a tortilla chip-full into your mouth-your tastebuds will love this Queso's restaurant quality 
flavor, and your wallet will appreciate you skipping the takeout. 

For vegetarian nachos, drizzle a generous helping of Queso over a plate of White Corn Tortilla Chips [sku 
95347], then cover them with crumbled Soy Chorizo [sku 92463] and Hot & Sweet Jalapeños, if you're feeling 
especially spicy. Or, pay homage to Tijuana, Mexico's quesabirria tacos by spreading some Queso Dip onto 
Corn Tortillas [sku 92394], topping them with Beef Birria [sku 72620], folding them over into tacos, and pan 
frying until crispy and melty. Don't forget to save the birria juice for dipping!

White Queso Dip
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Cheese Board","Crack a Beer","Effortless Entertaining","Game Night","Midday Snacks","Picnic"]

title: Sweet Chili Sauce
description:
Trader Joe's Sweet Chili Sauce is our authentic take on the sweet-hot blend of chilies and garlic used in 
kitchens across Thailand. Our supplier adds whole red chilies and Thai garlic to a sweet & sour-like concoction, 
creating a versatile sauce that can be used as a condiment, dip, stir-fry sauce, or appetizer component. We 
like it on burgers and Korean Style Short Ribs [sku 90809], or brushed on chicken before grilling. It's a natural 
for dipping things like gyoza, egg rolls or Chicken Spring Rolls [sku 55571]. You may try grilling peaches or 
nectarines and dipping them in Sweet Chili Sauce. It's also surprisingly delicious served over softened cream 
cheese and served with crackers - a quick, super-easy hors d'oeuvre that will leave your guests begging for the 
"recipe." You'll find each 10.1-fluid ounce bottle of Trader Joe's Sweet Chili Sauce, every day in our grocery 
aisle.

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Sweet Chili Sauce

title: Thick, Bold & Spicy Red Sauce
description:
When it comes to pasta sauces, we offer more variety than we do in some other food categories. While you 
may only desire the singular, best Organic Ketchup [sku 55860] to satisfy your ketchup cravings, your cravings 
for different styles of pasta sauce may fluctuate day to day, meal to meal. With this in mind, we concluded that 
our assortment of sauces was missing a richer, bolder, tomato-based option. This is where Trader Joe's Thick, 
Bold & Spicy Red Sauce comes in!

The name sort of says it all, but let's break it down a bit... This Red Sauce begins as any homemade tomato 
sauce might, with diced tomatoes in juice, tomato paste, garlic, diced onion, and oil (we opted for extra virgin 
olive oil here). The addition of basil, honey, and sun-dried tomatoes work together to develop a more nuanced 
flavor profile than a standard red sauce. So far, so Bold-where's the Spicy? The heat comes with a carefully 
concocted combo of peppers that includes crushed red pepper, ancho chili pepper powder, black pepper, and 
paprika. Finally, all these ingredients are simmered until reaching a Thick, rich texture.

Trader Joe's Thick, Bold & Spicy Red Sauce is so good on all kinds of pasta, from Organic Spaghetti [sku 
78011] to Chickpea Fusilli [sku 78268]. Beyond pasta, it also works incredibly well as a tasty dipping sauce for 
your oven-warmed Ciabatta Baguette [sku 96398], or for TJ's ready-to-bake Organic Garlic Bread [sku 77219]. 
You'll find sixteen-ounce jars of Thick, Bold & Spicy Red Sauce on our shelves among a variety of delicious 
pasta sauces, every day!

Thick, Bold & Spicy Red Sauce
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","Family Style","Pair With Wine"]

title: Enchilada Sauce
description:
Enchiladas might just be the very definition of comfort food: layers of hearty rolled tortillas, rich, savory, and 
often meaty fillings, gloriously melty cheese...and, of course, vividly full-flavored sauce to bind it all together. 
In fact, the sauce might just be the most important element of enchiladas to get right, which is why we proudly 
carry Trader Joe's Enchilada Sauce on our shelves. It's made for us by a trusted supplier, who starts with a 
base of tomato paste and red jalapeño purée, then seasons it with ground red chiles, onion, garlic, and chipotle 
pepper powder. What they don't use are any gums, natural flavors, or artificial preservatives, so that your 
homemade enchiladas will taste homemade, every time.

Savory, smoky, and ever-so-slightly spicy, our bold and full-flavored Enchilada Sauce won't just make your 
enchiladas tastier, they'll make them a lot easier, too: simply roll corn or flour torillas up with your favorite 
fillings (we find it's a little easier if you fry the tortillas in oil for a second or two beforehand), line them up 
in a baking dish, cover with Enchilada Sauce and your favorite cheese, and bake! And if that wasn't enough, 
we also find that it's quite suited for making Mexican cuisine-inspired casseroles, or even using as a sauce for  
making chilaquiles, too.

Enchilada Sauce
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","Dinner Hack","In Lieu of Pizza"]

title: Thai Style Peanut Dressing
description:
When is a salad dressing more than a salad dressing? How about when it's also a great dip, condiment, marinade,  
sauce for a uniquely sweet and spicy pizza... All of these would make an entirely apt description for Trader 
Joe's Thai Style Peanut Dressing, but, truth be told, "Trader Joe's Thai Style Peanut Dressing (and Dip, and 
Condiment, and Marinade, and Pizza Sauce...)" just wouldn't quite fit on the bottle. It's made for us using the 
same recipe as the dressing found in Trader Joe's Crunchy Slaw [sku 80035], a longtime Crew and customer 
favorite in our West Coast stores, where its complex mix of sweet, savory, and spicy flavors earned it a spot as 
a solo act in Trader Joe's across the country.

Our Thai Style Peanut Dressing is so versatile, that even within just the context of salads, it's marvelously 
multifaceted: we recommend it for everything from light, leafy salads to hearty slaws, all the way to creamy 
pasta and potato salads, too. As for its dip qualifications, give it a spin with spring rolls or savory meat skewers. 
As a condiment, it's excellent on burgers and bánh mì-inspired creations. It makes a magnificent marinade for 
grilled chicken wings or steak, and a super sauce for a Thai-style pizza with chicken breast, cilantro, and sliced 
green onion.

Thai Style Peanut Dressing

title: Hoisin Sauce
description:
Named for the Cantonese word for "seafood," hoisin sauce gets its moniker not by virtue of containing 
seafood as an ingredient (it traditionally contains no animal-derived products, sea-based or not), nor by being 
specifically designed for serving with seafood (although it is, indeed, great with fish.) Rather, its title comes 
from the fact that its rich aromas and umami undertones evoke an ineffable, subtly seafood-y quality that's 
celebrated in Szechuan cuisine. To that, we'd also add that a great hoisin sauce, like Trader Joe's Hoisin Sauce, 
also expresses a certain sticky sweetness, savory character, and velvety texture that make it one of the more 
versatile condiments you'll ever find.

Made for us by a supplier in Thailand, who starts with a base of fermented soy bean paste, black sesame paste, 
and brown sugar, each batch of our full-flavored Hoisin Sauce is seasoned with a blend of aromatic spices like 
star anise, garlic powder, coriander seed, and Szechuan peppercorns. You may have had hoisin with roast duck, 
spring rolls, and noodle soups before-all excellent pairings, but that's hardly where we'd stop. We recommend 
drizzling our Hoisin over stir-fried vegetables, fried rice, bánh mì sandwiches, burgers, barbecued ribs, grilled 
shrimp or salmon, or even just using it as a sweet and savory dip for Fries [sku 96143].

Hoisin Sauce

title: Chicken Uncured Bacon Ranch Dip
description:
There's a group of ingredients that have been trending online for quite a while amongst lovers of savory, 
comforting recipes. This combination comes in the form of casseroles, skillet meals, sheet-pan recipes, 
sandwiches, salads, and even dips. In fact, this combo is the inspiration for Trader Joe's Chicken Uncured 
Bacon Ranch Dip!

Our version starts with a mixture of sour cream, shredded sharp Cheddar, cream cheese, mayo, and buttermilk. 
This creates a rich, creamy, cheesy base with a hint of tanginess. Then we add plenty of shredded, rotisserie-
style Chicken breast and pieces of Uncured Bacon. (Uncured, meaning there are no nitrites or nitrates added, 
except what's naturally occurring in sea salt and celery juice.) As if cheese, Chicken, and Bacon weren't enough, 
we finish the recipe with a custom, Ranch-style seasoning blend of herbs & spices, including chives, parsley, 
dill, garlic & onion.

While you can eat it cold, this Dip is really made to be heated. That's as easy as putting it in a microwave-safe 
bowl, and heating it 2-3 minutes at 30-second intervals until it's heated through. Then comes the dipping! 
The dip-list is limitless, but you might start with celery sticks, Les Petite Carrots of Many Colors [sku 57285], 
Pita Bite Crackers [sku 90701], Fall Leaf Tortilla Chips [sku 66065], and slices of toasted Organic Baguette [sku 
53835].

Chicken Uncured Bacon Ranch Dip

title: Sweet Potato Habanero Hot Sauce
description:
In the collective imagination, autumn flavors aren't typically associated with a whole lot of heat, per se-and if 
you ask us, that's a shame. As we approach the autumn months, and temperatures begin to lower, it's the perfect 
time for hearty chilis, capsaicin-loaded curries, super-spicy soups, and red-hot roasted veggies and proteins of 
all kinds. In support of this autumnal argument, we submit Trader Joe's Sweet Potato Habanero Hot Sauce. 
Made for us by a famed hot sauce supplier out of Atlanta, Georgia, each batch is made from a base of vinegar, 
sweet potatoes, and habanero peppers, as well as a mix of autumnally-appropriate spices like cinnamon, ginger, 
allspice, and cloves.

This marriage of peppery heat and fall flavors results in a one-of-a-kind Hot Sauce that's as versatile as it is 
unique. Aside from its use in the afore-mentioned hearty soups and roasts that autumn is known for, it also 
goes great with everyday fare like pizza, chicken wings, tacos, and all sorts of savory breakfast options. And for 
a fiery, dip that makes a great late summer or early autumn appetizer, simply mix a teaspoon or two with Greek 
Yogurt [sku 69707] and enjoy with French fries or Tots [sku 94904].

Sweet Potato Habanero Hot Sauce
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","Feeling Adventurous","Mouth On Fire","Pour It On","Put An Egg On It"]

title: Pizza Sauce
description:
At Trader Joe's, a product doesn't pass muster just once-it must do so again and again, long after it launches, 
to ensure our customers are as excited about it as our tasting panel was when it was first presented. Recently, 
our buyer applied this standard for satisfaction and deliciousness to our preexisting pizza sauce, and knew we 
could do better. And after a few rounds of tasting and tweaking an array of sauce options, we did-allow us to 
(re)introduce Trader Joe's Pizza Sauce! 

With a bright tomato flavor and more subtly seasoned profile than its predecessor, this Pizza Sauce provides a 
savory base layer that complements pizza toppings without overpowering them, and makes for a mighty tasty 
Breaded Mozzarella Cheese Sticks [sku 50209] dip, too. An added bonus: it's packed into shelf-stable jars, so you 
can always have a jar of Pizza Sauce at the ready when the craving strikes. 

In addition to our tasting panel standards for satisfaction and delicious, this kosher-certified Sauce passes 
muster when it comes to value, too. If "pizza party" is in your day planner, pop on over to your neighborhood 
Trader Joe's, where you'll find jars of Pizza Sauce on our grocery shelves for an incredible price, every day.

Pizza Sauce
tags: ["Crack a Beer","Dinner Hack","Family Style","Let's Bake!","Pour It On"]

title: Ponzu Sauce
description:
If you've ever been to a restaurant that serves poke, chances are that you've already experienced the uniquely 
tart, tangy, and umami-rich flavor of ponzu. Traditionally made with a base of rice vinegar, bonito broth, rice 
wine, and some manner of citrus juice, ponzu is a pitch-perfect sauce for seasoning fish for poke and sashimi, 
but that's hardly where we'd stop. Made for us by an expert supplier in Japan, Trader Joe's Ponzu Sauce can 
add an element of sweetness, savoriness, and richness to all sorts of dishes, from the simplest of rice bowls to 
the most complex of marinades.

Trader Joe's Ponzu Sauce is made in the style of shoyu ponzu, meaning it has a soy sauce base-ponzu without 
soy sauce tends to not keep very well on the shelf. Our supplier's recipe also subs out the rice wine in favor of 
a bit of sugar to provide a sweet contrast to the delightfully tart yuzu juice used in every batch. We find that 
this balance of ingredients makes it a more-than-capable condiment for pretty much any savory application in 
the kitchen, and especially so for making flavorful salad dressings, dipping with tempura, pan-fried gyoza, and 
other crispy appetizers, or mixing into burger patties for an extra bonito-powered boost of umami.

Ponzu Sauce

title: Yuzu Miso Topping & Spread
description:
Combining two iconically Japanese ingredients into one uniquely delicious sauce, Trader Joe's Yuzu Miso 
Topping & Spread is a curiously captivating condiment, unlike any other we've offered before. On tasting it, 
you'll likely first notice its rich, luxuriously thick consistency, then the savory, umami-filled notes of its white 
miso paste base, which perfectly leads into the pleasantly tart tones of its mixed-in yuzu zest and yuzu juice. 
Then, once you've had a chance to take it all in, the elegant balance between its savory and citric elements ought 
to immediately inspire you with all the possibilities for where you can use it..

And indeed, the possibilities are practically endless: it's spectacular spread over grilled seafood, it's stupendous 
on a seared steak, and it adds remarkable depth of flavor to roast chicken. But that's just the beginning. From 
the simple (drizzled over a bowl of plain white rice, dunked with Handsome Cut Potato Fries [sku 96143] 
or Organic Chicken Nuggets [sku 67594]) to the sophisticated (mixed into marinades for pork ribs, served 
alongside charcuterie boards, or as a spread for an especially ornate sandwich), Trader Joe's Yuzu Miso 
Topping & Spread will add an unmistakeably umami, tantalizingly tart element to them all.

Yuzu Miso Topping & Spread

title: Organic Mango Vinaigrette Dressing
description:
As it turns out, summertime salads positively shine when dressed in a fusion of sweet, tangy, and tropical 
flavors... And lucky for you, Trader Joe's Organic Mango Vinaigrette Dressing deftly incorporates each of 
these attributes, setting the table for some fantastically fresh, summer fare.

A fairly simple blend of organic mango purée, vegetable oil, distilled white vinegar, and cane sugar (plus organic 
orange juice concentrate, dried red bell peppers, and garlic powder for added vim and vigor), our Organic 
Mango Vinaigrette lends itself to all sorts of applications. You can, of course, add a splash to salads (spinach 
+ feta + toasted almonds + Organic Mango Vinaigrette = yum), or you can use it as a marinade for grilled 
chicken. Or as a fancy inclusion for fish tacos. Or as the star of a cold noodle dish or pasta salad... 

Organic Mango Vinaigrette Dressing

title: Yuzu Kosho
description:
The trick behind many great hot sauces and spicy condiments is a balance between tartness and heat-in 
a classic Buffalo sauce, for example, this is most often achieved via a carefully calibrated ratio of vinegar to 
cayenne. However, in the case of yuzu kosho, a chili paste popular in Japanese cuisine, it's less of a balancing act 
and more of a gleeful deep dive into both ends of the spectrum. Made with a captivating combination of chili 
peppers, sea salt, and peel of yuzu (a citrus that's downright essential in Japanese cuisine), Trader Joe's Yuzu 
Kosho offers thrilling heat, invigorating zestiness, and even a touch of umami in every bracing bite.

Our Yuzu Kosho's savory, sour, and spicy notes make it a more-than-capable condiment for all kinds of 
applications: it's an excellent spread for a sandwich, a terrific topper for freshly-seared scallops, and a superb 
sauce for spicing up a slice of pizza. Try mixing it into your next marinade for barbecued chicken wings, or 
adding a spoonful to a salad dressing for a little extra oomph. And for a truly special dip for French fries, Tots 
[sku 94094], and Organic Chicken Nuggets [sku 67594], add a bit of Yuzu Kosho to a small bowl of mayonnaise 
and sprinkle with Furikake [sku 60255].

Yuzu Kosho

title: French Vinaigrette with Shallots
description:
A great salad dressing should accomplish three things: for starters, it shouldn't be too thick-at that point, 
it's just dip. Second, it should expertly complement your salad ingredients. And third, it should of course, be 
delicious. We're delighted to report that Trader Joe's French Vinaigrette with Shallots handily meets these 
salad dressing standards.

Sporting a signature tanginess courtesy of red wine vinegar and Dijon mustard, this French Vinaigrette with 
Shallots offers from-scratch flavor without the hassle that tends to accompany from-scratch preparation. Its 
subtle, sophisticated flavors and easily poured nature create a classic Paris bistro vibe wherever you splash 
it-on Little Gem Lettuce [sku 76869], in a marinade for chicken or fish, over of-the-moment veggies (think 
steamed Artichokes [sku 76894] or grilled Zucchini [sku 20491]), or in a picnic-ready pasta salad. (Give the 
bottle a good shake prior to use-just like a from-scratch dressing, you won't find gums or thickeners here!)

This authentic, made-in-France classic is an astonishing value-and now available on the grocery shelves at 
your neighborhood Trader Joe's, every day.

French Vinaigrette with Shallots

title: Soy Sauce Reduced Sodium
description:
Everyone knows soy sauce is salty. It's like the Asian-cuisine equivalent to a shaker of table salt. People use it 
liberally to add verve to all kinds of dishes, from stir-frys and noodle soups-to meats and vegetables. Just a 
little transforms bland white rice into something of a meal. And when it comes to recipes, it often serves as the 
base for sauces and marinades.

Despite its popularity, soy sauce's saltiness (say that ten times fast!) also means high sodium-something more 
and more people are choosing to avoid. Accordingly, the only soy sauce we sell is Trader Joe's Reduced Sodium 
Soy Sauce. With 530mg of sodium per 1 Tbsp. serving, it contains about 50% less sodium than leading soy 
sauce brands. Lower sodium aside, our Soy Sauce is made with the traditional Honjozo method, which uses 
a 6 month to 2 year natural brewing and fermentation approach. This means Trader Joe's Reduced Sodium 
Soy Sauce tastes authentic and is ideal for all your soy sauce needs. We're pretty sure you won't even notice the 
missing sodium!

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Reduced Sodium Soy Sauce

title: Organic 100% Sicilian Lemon Juice
description:
You know what they say-when life gives you gorgeous, sun-kissed, Sicilian-grown lemons, make Organic 
100% Sicilian Lemon Juice! Cultivated on the island of Sicily since the 10th century (it isn't called the "Lemon 
Riviera" for nothing), Sicilian lemons are known for their aromatic, slightly oily peels and bright, sour-yet-
slightly-less-acidic flavor-and Trader Joe's Organic 100% Sicilian Lemon Juice captures the essence of an 
Italian lemon grove in a bottle. 

We know what you're thinking: "Gee, Trader Joe's, couldn't I just squeeze my own organic lemons?" Why, 
certainly you can! Easy-peasy lemon-squeezy, as they say. But squeezing your own organic Silcilian lemons 
might be a little trickier, as Sicilian lemons aren't as commonly found in stateside stores. Plus, you simply can't 
argue with the sheer convenience of having not-from-concentrate Lemon Juice on-demand. And whereas 
most bottled lemon juice is made from concentrate and infused with preservatives, ours contains nothing but 
pure, freshly-pressed & pasteurized Organic 100% Sicilian Lemon Juice. That's it. Whether you're a seasoned 
chef, a budding mixologist, or simply someone who appreciates a high-quality product at an incredible price, 
it's sure to earn a permanent spot in your pantry. 

Organic 100% Sicilian Lemon Juice

title: Cowboy Caviar Salsa
description:
Legend has it that the Cowboy Caviar concept was originally developed around 1930 for an "all Texas" 
menu at a high-end department store. The head chef was mandated to include black-eyed-peas on the menu.  
Since she personally loathed the legumes, to make them palatable, she pickled them with onions, creating a 
salad-esque salsa -- "Cowboy Caviar" --  that has since become a cult classic.  

Strap on your spurs, Trader Joe's Cowboy Caviar is now in your town. Since we love cult classics, 
especially of the crazy, creative culinary concoction class, and we've had good success with our other less-
than-ordinary salsas, we decided to create our very own Trader Joe's Cowboy Caviar. Instead of black-
eyed peas, however, our "caviar" of choice is black beans that are mixed together with corn, onions and 
red bell peppers. Pickled in a blend of chipotle peppers, adobo sauce and lime juice, this crunchy, savory 
salsation carries southwestern character and enough heat to take note. It's a natural partner to tortilla chips 
and makes a delicious fish taco topping. Gluten-free, fat-free, low in sodium and vegan, Cowboy Caviar 
has "cult-classic character" written all over it, especially at just $2.49 for a 13 ounce jar. Yee-haw!

(This is not the actual jar)

CORRECTION: Cowboy Caviar Corn, Black Bean & Pepper Salsa does contain tomato as an ingredient. The 
information on this sheet has been amended to accurately reflect the correct salsa composition. Thank you.

title: Glaze
description:
¿  
 

Balsamic Glaze 
Trader Joe's Balsamic Glaze was born of the desire to have a rich, thick, creamy 
balsamic glaze available and within arm's reach, without having to take the time to 
reduce our own balsamic vinegar every time the craving struck.  And that's exactly 
what's inside this squeeze bottle. 
 
Balsamic Glaze is made for us in Modena, Italy, home of some of the world's best 
balsamic vinegar.  It's crafted using traditional methods, so it has the deep flavor and 
pungent aroma you expect. You can, of course, reduce balsamic vinegar over a flame to 
achieve a similar consistency, but that takes precious time and tends to increase the 
acidity of the vinegar.  Our Balsamic Glaze is ready to use and it preserves an ideal 
balance of sweet and bitter.  It's made by combining concentrated grape must and 
balsamic vinegar, then using a special filtration process that results in the thicker 
consistency that makes this Glaze so versatile.  Use it on salads, as a drizzle over grilled 
meat and fish, or as a dessert topping for fresh, summertime berries.  We're selling each 
8.5 fluid ounce bottle for $2.99, every day, making it a time saver and a money saver!
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Cheese Board","Date Night","Feeling Fancy","Gild The Lily","Pour It On","The \"X\" Factor"]

title: Reduced Guilt Spinach & Kale Greek Yogurt Dip
description:
Trader Joe's S&KGYD (that's Spinach & Kale Greek Yogurt Dip, as the header up above might have indicated) 
is a downright delicious. And thanks to its key ingredients-specifically, low-fat Greek yogurt-it has just 2g 
of fat & 30 calories per two-tablespoon serving. That's 75% less fat than regular spinach dip made with sour 
cream. Every tub is packed with Spinach & Kale, with finely chopped water chestnuts, red peppers, carrots, 
green onions, garlic on board contributing major flavor and texture. The recipe includes with a bit of mayo for 
extra smoothness, and just a touch of agave nectar to add subtle sweetness.  

S&KGYD is a natural choice to pair with fresh vegetable crudités or crackers and a superstar on sandwiches 
in place of mayo or other traditional condiments-whether it's turkey & cheese, piled high roast beef, an 
abundance of roasted vegetables, or even a freshly grilled burger, the flavor & texture of this Dip really shine.  

TJ's S&KGYD is made exclusively for us, so you'll find it only in the refrigerated case at your neighborhood 
Trader Joe's. We're selling each 16-ounce tub for the excellent everyday price of $4.49.

Spinach & Kale Greek Yogurt Dip

title: Thai Peanut Satay Sauce
description:
Satay may be the one of most celebrated street foods in the history of global cuisine. Originating in Malaysia 
possibly as far back as the 1400s, love for satay has spread across Southeast Asia in the ensuing centuries, 
including the Philippines, Thailand, Sri Lanka, and Indonesia, where it has since been enshrined as a national 
dish. Now a favorite among foodies the world over, the popularity of satay skewers has brought with it a 
commensurate appreciation for satay sauce (also known as sambal kacang.) As our very own Trader Joe's Thai 
Peanut Satay Sauce demonstrates, this sweet, savory, and lightly spicy peanut-based sauce makes the ideal 
accompaniment to a classic chicken satay skewer-and so much more, too.

Made for us by a supplier in Thailand, our Peanut Satay Sauce starts with a base of rich coconut milk, peanuts, 
and aromatic red curry paste, to which our supplier adds a mix of savory seasonings including lemongrass, 
shallot, garlic, galangal, and tamarind paste. In addition to making a delicious dipping sauce for grilled, 
skewered proteins of all kinds (we're especially fond of it with shrimp, pork loin, or tofu), it also makes a 
fantastic condiment for burgers and lettuce wraps, and a superb sauce for serving over Thai Wheat Noodles 
[sku 62742]. And for an effortless and flavorful salad dressing, simply add a bit of Rice Vinegar [sku 76721] to  
a few spoonfuls of Satay Sauce in a bowl, mix, and enjoy.

Thai Peanut Satay Sauce

title: Rosatella Pasta Sauce
description:
When it's pasta night, if you have a hard time choosing between the tangy brightness of marinara and the silky 
creaminess of alfredo-then don't! Enjoy the best of both worlds with Trader Joe's Rosatella Pasta Sauce.

This "pink sauce" really delivers on flavor, and it's no wonder considering the quality of what goes into the jar. 
Our supplier in Italy sources all of their dairy from the Piedmont region-a region renowned for its milk and 
cheeses. They start with a cream & milk blend, to which they add a short list of ingredients, including tomato 
paste, onion & garlic purées, basil, oregano, and Grana Padano PDO cheese. 

Boil your favorite TJ's pasta until it's al dente, then drain and mix with our Rosatella Pasta Sauce. The bright 
tomato flavor and lavish creaminess create a truly delicious and authentically Italian eating experience!

Rosatella Pasta Sauce

title: Italian Bomba Hot Pepper Sauce
description:
There's a great big world of hot sauces out there, from the straightforward and simple (like our Chili Pepper 
Sauce [sku 92484] to the deceptively versatile (like our Sriracha Sauce [sku 50828]). Some hot sauces blast you 
with heat upfront, thrilling your taste buds with immediate urgency. Others subtly sneak in heat, coupling their 
capsicum with complementary sensations and flavors. And others still, like Trader Joe's Italian Bomba Hot 
Pepper Sauce, build heat, bite by bite, until you reach a crescendo of spice so invigorating, that it paradoxically 
keeps you coming back for more.

Made with Calabrian chili peppers sourced from a trusted pepper cultivator in Calabria, Italy (the "toe" of Italy's 
"boot," if you will), our Italian Bomba Hot Sauce is our tribute to a centuries-old culinary tradition. Since 
the 1500s, Calabrian hot chili peppers have been a staple of Southern Italian cuisine, especially when crushed, 
fermented, and mixed into a firey hot condiment, just like this Bomba Sauce. The natural fruity notes of the 
peppers are amplified by the slightly pickled flavor and texture they take on during fermentation, making it 
particularly suited for pasta dishes and pizzas. And, like a ticking time bomb ("Bomba" is Italian for bomb, after 
all), the more you eat, the more heat develops, until it (and whatever you put it on) is bursting with flavor.

While most specialty Italian grocers might charge you upwards of $8 or $9 for a jar of Calabrian pepper sauce, at 
Trader Joe's, you can find our 6.7-ounce jars of Italian Bomba Hot Pepper Sauce, made from authentic Calabrian 
chilies and authentically imported from Italy, for the steaming hot price of $2.99. Look for them in our Grocery aisle.

07.29.
19
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Feeling Adventurous","Mouth On Fire","Pair With Wine"]

title: Guacasalsa
description:
There's more to an avocado than just guacamole, and one need look no further than Trader Joe's Guacasalsa 
for proof. This tangy, tantalizing take on a classic salsa de aguacate is made with a base of tart tomatillos and 
creamy avocados, to which our supplier adds jalapeños for spice, cilantro for aromatic herbiness, garlic purée 
for a savory edge, and a touch of lime juice to keep everything in balance. All together, this sublimely simple 
recipe results in super smooth and satisfying salsa that's great for dipping with chips, mixing into sauces, or 
spooning over pretty much anything you can think of.

Seriously: try it on homemade nachos, atop a burger, drizzled over a brown rice bowl with seared salmon and 
roasted broccolini...Guacasalsa will bring a burst of bright, lightly spicy flavor to them all. When it comes to 
dipping, feel free to think beyond chips, too: we love them with our Chicken, Cheese & Green Chile Pupusas 
[sku 75475], crispy empanadas, French fries and tater tots, or our Buffalo Style Chicken Poppers [sku 61202].  
And at the breakfast table, we're particularly partial to giving the Guacasalsa treatment to omelets, chilaquiles, 
eggs Benedict, and quiches of all kinds.

Guacasalsa
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","Effortless Entertaining","Game Night","Midday Snacks","Picnic"]

title: Roasted Garlic Marinara Sauce
description:
Maybe its just us, but the smell of a luscious red sauce heating up in harmony with boiling pasta is a nostalgic 
memory of a simple dinner of yesteryear. But unlike many meals from our childhoods, a simple weeknight 
spaghetti and marinara dinner is still a staple that evokes heartiness, warmth, and family even into adulthood. 
And boy, can Trader Joe's Roasted Garlic Marinara get you there within minutes of cracking open a fresh jar.

We start with a classic tomato puree base and crank up the flavors from there; soybean oil, salt, sugar, roasted 
garlic, and plenty of parsley, basil, and oregano to be precise. A traditional whirlwind of flavors, but an ideal 
balance of each one comes together to make our Roasted Garlic Marinara as delightfully delicious as if you 
were enjoying an authentic Italian dinner during a night out on the town. But we don't require a reservation, 
suit and tie, or parking validation for this authentically Italian Roasted Garlic Marina sauce to be enjoyed. And 
don't limit yourself to pasta recipes, think of this mouthwatering Marinara as just the beginning of shakshuka,  
minestrone, ratatouille, or a creamy tomato soup. All waiting, at your finger tips, once you pop the top of this 
shelf-stable sauce.

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Roasted Garlic Marinara

title: Fall Harvest Salsa
description:
In Spanish, salsa simply means "sauce," but English speakers have adopted the term to reference a spicy, Mex-
ican-style condiment used for dipping. Maybe that's the kind of salsa you're thinking of when you hear about 
our Fall Harvest Salsa-you're probably thinking: tomatoes, onions, jalapeños; diced and mixed, ready for chip 
dipping. 

You'd only be partly right! Take your North American idea of salsa and move it north and east, to New England. 
Now flip the calendar forward to autumn. Remove those tomatoes and replace them with fire-roasted tomatillos. 
Add in some honey-roasted, heirloom Dickinson pumpkin chunks, and diced butternut squash. Balance those 
slightly spicy jalapeños with some chopped sweet apples, and pull it all together with honey, vinegar, and lime. 
We call this the "salsification of New England¿ with a Latin twist."

Our Fall Harvest Salsa melds fantastic fall flavors with the brightness and heat you expect from a typical salsa. 
It's the perfect balance of earthy, sweet, tangy, and spicy. Open up a jar and pair it with our Organic Blue Corn 
Tortilla Chips [sku 94583] for your football-watching friends. Invite the Mediterranean to the party when you 
spread some Fat Free Ricotta Cheese [sku 95458] on our Fig & Olive Crisps [sku 53273] with a spoonful of Fall 
Harvest Salsa on top-an amazing crostini appetizer at your next seasonal party. You could even empty an 
entire jar into a saucepan, add Organic Vegetable Broth [sku 21509], and heat it up until you have a stupendous, 
salsified, autumnal soup!

However you enjoy it, Trader Joe's Fall Harvest Salsa is an incomparable way to welcome the crisp, cool days 
of autumn. Each 12-ounce, shelf-stable jar is available on our grocery shelves for only $2.99.

9.14.1
5

title: Almond Chipotle Dip
description:
Sometimes, a product comes through our tasting panel that's so fun, flavorful, and immediately habit-forming 
that we know, then and there, we have something special on our hands. Trader Joe's Almond Chipotle Dip 
is such a product. Made with a base of smooth and creamy almond butter, and flavored with smoky and 
savory seasonings like chipotle pepper powder, smoked paprika, garlic, and tamari, as soon as our panel tried 
this pleasantly peppery, vegan Dip, excitement and ideas rapidly began to spread: "This would go great with 
something cool and crunchy, like Jicama Sticks [sku 55482]!" "I'd love to try this on a nice piece of BBQ Cut 
Salmon [sku 24455]..." "Ooh, what about on top of a Quinoa Cowboy Veggie Burger [sku 53276]?" 

We're happy to report that all these ideas are right on the money. It's scrumptious when scooped with your 
favorite chip, cracker, or crudités (we're especially fond of using it as a supplemental sauce for our Vegetable 
Tray [sku 77630]), it's splendid as a spread on a sandwich, burger, or wrap, and it's sensational as a sauce for 
lighter proteins like poultry, fish, and tofu. And since it's vegan, it also makes a great alternative to dairy-based 
topping for homemade nachos, baked potatoes, and Battered Plant-Based Fish Fillet [sku 74251] tacos.

Almond Chipotle Dip
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Cheese Board","Crack a Beer","Feeling Adventurous","Game Night","Midday Snacks","Picnic"]

title: Crunchy Chili Onion Hummus
description:
We do our best to remain humble about our hummus selection, but it's not always easy-especially when we 
have humdingers like Trader Joe's Crunchy Chili Onion Hummus among our ranks. Made with a base of 
creamy, puréed chickpeas and sesame seeds, as well as a bit of sunflower oil and sea salt, our supplier finishes 
each batch with with a dollop of our acclaimed customer fave, Crunchy Chili Onion [sku 62480]. This addition 
gives every bite a pop of savory garlic, aromatic onion, and spicy red chili, along with an accompanying crunch, 
which all serve to complement its superbly smooth texture.

An ideal dip for chips, crackers, and crudites of all kinds, our Crunchy Chili Onion Hummus is an excellent  
option for an appetizer or anytime snack. We also find that its creamy consistency and lively levels of allium and 
heat notes make it especially suited for spreading on sandwiches, wraps, and burgers-we're particularly fond 
of pairing it with our Quinoa Cowbie Veggie Burgers [sku 53276], for instance. And for a full (and full-flavored) 
meal, make our Crunchy Chili Onion Hummus part of a Mediterranean-style meze plate, along with other 
favorites like our Falafel [sku 65633], Dolmas [sku 50752], and Authentic Greek Feta in Brine [sku 86232].

Crunchy Chili Onion Hummus

title: Organic Marinara Sauce
description:
What's the best sauce to add to your Organic Italian Gigli Pasta [sku 60942]. Of course, there are untold 
possibilities - even within the four walls of Trader Joe's you could fill a shopping cart with saucing options. So 
how do you choose? Why not start with one of the runaway favorites for topping any kind of pasta¿ Trader 
joe's Organic Marinara Sauce. It's the epitome of a "simple sauce," but don't assume simple equals boring. 
Here, simple means organically-grown, vine-ripened, California tomatoes that have been steam peeled, sorted, 
and diced. They're puréed, blended with organic tomato paste, organic Parmesan cheese, and seasonings, then 
simmered in small batches until the ideal sauce texture and flavor is achieved. The resultant sauce is medium-
thick with robust tomato flavor, accented by a bit of nuttiness from the Parmesan and a finishing flourish of 
basil. Your pasta will be psyched to meet this Sauce. Then again, so will your pizza, your lasagna, your Chicken 
Parm, your roasted fish, or your crusty bread.

Your wallet will be equally psyched to meet our Organic Marinara, given our price of $2.49* for each 25-ounce 
jar. You'll find it in our grocery aisle, with our other, equally extraordinary pasta sauces.

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Organic Marinara Sauce

title: Sriracha Sauce
description:
Sriracha Sauce is named for central Thailand's coastal city of Si Racha, and modeled after the kicking chili 
paste condiment that is ubiquitous at local seafood restaurants. In the realm of hot sauce - Sriracha is Hot. 
Restaurants, professional kitchens, family tables... It's turning up all over the culinary landscape, imparting 
heat, tang and boldness. We know what you're thinking; if it is everywhere already, why is it coming 
to Trader Joe's only now? It's not because we're chicken; it's because we wanted to deliver the quality, 
without the "funky" ingredients that load up other cock-sure versions in the marketplace. After years of 
experimenting with chili crops and identifying the other critical components to craft a compelling Sriracha

title: Soyaki
description:
Savory garlic, zesty ginger and preservative-free soy sauce form the flavor base for this unique, Asian-style 
sauce that's become a mainstay in our grocery aisle. You might think it's just another teriyaki sauce - you'd be 
wrong. It's so much more than that. In addition to its sweet, savory, and spicy ingredients, where this sauce 
veers from the everyday is in the addition of sesame seeds to the mix. The seeds add flavor and texture, setting 
Trader Joe's Soyaki quite apart from the crowd. Remember to give the bottle a good shake before using - this 
will ensure the seeds are dispersed throughout the sauce, ensuring maximum seed exposure and an excellent 
Soyaki experience.

Try Trader Joe's Soyaki as a marinade for chicken, beef, pork or shrimp - the slightly sweet flavor of the sauce 
is equally delicious grilled, broiled, pan sautéed or baked. Use it as a stir-fry sauce for veggies and tofu. It makes 
a good dip for gyoza or shu mai. You may even find yourself drinking it straight from the bottle - we're not 
recommending this, but who are we to judge? You'll find our 21-ounce Soyaki on our grocery shelves. 
  
 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Soyaki

title: Traditional Tunisian Harissa
description:
What ketchup is to the United States, Harissa is to Tunisia. So much so, it is often dubbed as the "national 
condiment of Tunisia." That's dedication. And we think such delicious dedication should be recognized; Trader 
Joe's Traditional Tunisian Harissa is our authentic and tasty little 'shout out.' 

No need to guess where we acquired this pleasing paste -just look at the title. Our Harissa Hot Chili 
Pepper Paste hails from the land where they know best how to make Harissa. And, we think our 
Tunisian supplier is the best-of-the-best. The paste is prepared in small batches with fresh, red chiles 
that are grilled in a tumbler over an open flame, and blended with a traditional mix of herbs and spices, 
including garlic, cumin, and caraway. This deep red concoction is smooth and spreadable, with a little 
smoke flavor (from the grilling), and a healthy amount of heat. Yes, it is as flavorfully divine as it sounds. 
Plus, this bold spread boasts only 10 calories, and a half-a-gram of fat per serving (one teaspoon). 

Create a traditional Tunisian dish with this Harissa atop Albacore Tuna in Olive Oil [sku 99287]. Or, enjoy this 
paste with grilled, diced Fresh Organic Chicken Breast [sku  63550], and Garbanzo Beans [sku 20829]. For a 
flavorful dip with a kick, stir some Harissa into our Smooth & Creamy Classic Hummus [sku 93590]. This is one 
of those special sauces that you will want to put on everything and anything, once you get a taste. 

We are offering a 6.7 ounce jar of Trader Joe's Traditional Tunisian Harissa for $2.69. Find it on our grocery 
shelves, sort of in the same vicinity as the ketchup.

09.05.
16

title: Lemon Pesto Sauce
description:
Some say that cooking is chemistry; others call it magic. When it comes to Trader Joe's Lemon Pesto Sauce, 
we're inclined toward the latter. Inspired by a pasta dish from Italy's Amalfi coast (where lemon is a key element 
of local cuisine), our Italian supplier crushes whole lemons and combines them with sunflower seed oil, savory 
Grana Padano cheese, almonds, a touch of salt, a pinch of black pepper, and extra lemon zest for good, citrusy 
measure. This enchanting concoction is light, bright, a little cheesy, a little nutty, and positively bursting with 
Lemon flavor-a dazzling example of culinary wizardry.

When we say this limited edition, lip-smacking Sauce adds magic to mealtimes, it's not hyperbole. Stir it into 
Organic Mafalda Corta Pasta [sku 75229] with Fresh Mozzarella Cheese Pearls [sku 76317] and chopped mint. 
Spread it on a toasted baguette and top with Sliced Prosciutto [sku 98861]. Dollop it on grilled All Natural Thin-
Sliced Chicken Breasts [96763] or shrimp kabobs. With each wave of your wand¿ er, spoon, you may even be 
inspired to incant "Presto, Lemon Pesto!"

Lemon Pesto Sauce

title: Chunky Garlic & Jalapeño Hot Sauce
description:
A hot sauce needs more than just heat to be great. A truly great hot sauce-and we're talking about the kind you 
can put on absolutely anything-needs to strike a balance between its savory, tart, textural, and spicy elements. 
And we're here to tell you today that Trader Joe's Chunky Garlic & Jalapeño Hot Sauce is a truly great hot 
sauce. Inside each bottle, Jalapeño and Garlic work hand in glove to produce a flavor profile that effortlessly 
balances savory and spicy, salty and sour, chunky and pourable, all in a way that makes it a marvelous match 
for tacos, eggs, nachos, potatoes, and pretty much anything else that could use an extra kick of flavor.

Made with a base of puréed, brined jalapeños and garlic grown in Gilory, CA (the "Garlic Capital of the World," 
no less!) our Chunky Garlic & Jalapeño Hot Sauce's relatively thick consistency, captivating aromatics, and 
steady, building heat all work together in harmony to create a consummate catch-all condiment. We especially 
like it over something warm and crispy, like a basket of freshly air-fried Seasoned Waffle Cut Fries [sku 73594]. 
Another hot tip: Our Chunky Garlic & Jalapeño Hot Sauce may just be your new best friend at the breakfast 
table. Try it on omelettes, homemade chilaquiles, a well-stacked breakfast sandwich, or even avocado toast.

Chunky Garlic & Jalapeño Hot Sauce
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Brunch All Day","Crack a Beer","Game Night","Mouth On Fire","Put An Egg On It"]

title: Roasted Red Pepper Hummus
description:
We do our best to remain humble about our hummus selection, but it's not always easy-especially when we 
have humdingers like Trader Joe's Roasted Red Pepper Hummus among our ranks. Made with a base of 
creamy, puréed chickpeas and sesame seeds, as well as a bit of sunflower oil and sea salt, our supplier finishes 
each batch with with a helping of rich, flavorful, roasted red peppers to tie it all together. Every bite is superbly 
savory and terrifically smooth-textured-the kind of hummus to leave you humming with excitement all day.

An ideal companion to Pita Chips [sku 91053], crackers, carrot sticks, cherry tomatoes, or pretty much anything 
that'll serve as a scoop, to be honest, Trader Joe's Roasted Red Pepper Hummus makes a great midday snack, 
pre-meal appetizer, or party hors d'oeuvre. We also find that its creamy consistency and delightfully peppery 
notes make it especially suited for spreading on sandwiches and wraps, and even more so when the sandwiches 
and wraps in question prominently feature other roasted veggies. And for a full (and full-flavored) meal, make 
our Roasted Red Pepper Hummus part of a Mediterranean-style meze plate, along with other favorites like our 
Tabbouli [sku 97118], Grecian Style Eggplant [sku 53896], and Feta, Pepper Drop, and Olive Antipasto [sku 67029].

Roasted Red Pepper Hummus
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Brunch All Day","Crack a Beer","Effortless Entertaining","Game Night","Midday Snacks"]

title: Thai Sweet Ginger Sauce
description:
Ginger is so utterly unique in its flavor, aroma, and even the physical sensations it creates in the mouth, that it 
almost feels like a culinary gift from nature itself. It's honestly hard to imagine what global cuisine would look 
like (or, more importantly, taste like) without this singularly scrumptious root. And now, there's an easy way to 
incorporate its inimitable flavor profile to any dish you wish: Trader Joe's Thai Sweet Ginger Sauce combines 
the savory, herby sensations of ginger with the rich sweetness of coconut sugar, a touch of pickled garlic, and 
just a bit of soy sauce to make one seriously versatile condiment. You get sweet, spicy, salty, and garlicky - all 
in a single sauce.

Made especially for us by a trusted supplier in Thailand, this Sweet Ginger Sauce is practically perfect for 
serving with a plate of pan-fried Pork Gyoza [sku 10602], but that's hardly where we'd stop. In fact, we find that 
its sweet, ginger-y heat makes for excellent dunking with all kinds of savory, meaty dishes, including chicken 
skewers, samosas, or crispy fried shrimp. Of course, we haven't forgotten plant-based options: try pouring a bit  
of our Thai Sweet Ginger Sauce over garlic-fried rice or sautéed Tempeh [sku 99125], or mix with a bit of olive 
oil and vinegar for a sweet, snappy salad dressing.

Thai Sweet Ginger Sauce

title: Tomato Basil Marinara Sauce
description:
Basil has a strong association with two very different culinary cultures; In Southeast Asia (particularly Thailand), 
a bolder, spicier basil is common, while in Italy, a sweeter version enhances many popular dishes. Trader Giotto's 
Tomato Basil Marinara is our personal ode to the flavor of sweet basil as it's so often enjoyed in its Italian 
context.

Ironically, neither tomatoes, nor basil originate in Italy. Tomatoes made their way eastward to Europe as late 
as the 16th century, when Spanish explorers brought newly discovered tomato plants back home from the 
Americas. Basil came westward, from India, via the ancient spice route. But, distant origins won't change the 
fact that tomatoes and basil taste like they are made for Marinara-like frescoes are made for the Sistine Chapel.

Giotto's Tomato Basil Marinara incorporates the usual suspects: tomato puree, tomatoes, oil (extra virgin olive 
and soybean), salt, sugar, garlic, onions, and spices (parsley and oregano, in addition to the basil). We've cooked 
everything down to a smooth, slightly chunky sauce that has a bright tomato taste, accented by moderate basil 
notes. Heat it 'as is' and serve over spaghetti, penne, or any kind of pasta. (Thai rice noodles might make an 
interesting partner!) Use it as a simmer sauce for chicken breasts or meatballs. Or, let it be the starting point for 
your own sauce-creation. So many different ways to enjoy this sauce. 

Each 26-ounce jar of Trader Giotto's Basil Marinara is just $1.79. Find it in our grocery aisle. (If it happens to 
be next to our Thai Red Curry Simmer Sauce [sku 57474] on the shelf, that's pure coincidence.) ... Or is it?
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Family Style","Pair With Wine","Pour It On","Stuff of Dreams"]

title: Buttermilk Ranch Dressing
description:
Since its invention in the middle of the 20th century, ranch has taken on a culinary life of its own. In addition 
to its status as the best-selling style of salad dressing in the U.S. for over three decades, it's also earned the 
title of best-selling condiment in the U.S. in recent years-even more so than ketchup! Beloved for how well 
its creamy, herby flavor profile enhances French fries, carrot sticks, chicken wings, pizza, and everything in 
between, ranch is a powerhouse of "put-it-on-everything" practicality, and Trader Joe's Buttermilk Ranch 
Dressing ably demonstrates why.

Each bottle is made with a classic recipe that starts with a base of cultured buttermilk, sour cream, and 
mayonnaise, and flavored with an array of aromatic herbs and seasonings including garlic, chives, dill, and 
shallots. Cool, creamy, and delightfully old-fashioned, our Buttermilk Ranch serves spectacularly well in 
a salad with nearly any leafy green [though we're particularly partial to one made with Butter Lettuce [sku 
94470]. Unsurprisingly, it also makes an excellent dip, condiment, or spread for all kinds of savory snacks, 
appetizers, or sandwiches, respectively. What might surprise you, however, is the fact that even with its rich, 
creamy consistency, each two-tablespoon serving contains only 70 calories.

Buttermilk Ranch Dressing
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","Family Style","Game Night","Picnic","Pour It On"]

title: Pico de Gallo Salsa Mild
description:
Also known in its native home of Mexico as "Salsa Bandera" (after the red, green, and white of the Mexican 
flag), pico de gallo is an icon in its own right: a perennial favorite for parties, a necessary accessory to nachos, 
and an absolute essential for any taco Tuesday (or taco any-other-day-of-the-week, for that matter.) Trader 
Joe's Mild Pico De Gallo is an edible tribute to this scion of salsas, an easy option for when you need fresh pico 
de gallo, but don't quite have the time for all that chopping.

Made in the classic style using diced tomatoes, onions, jalapeños, cilantro, and lemon juice, our Pico De Gallo 
isn't just an ideal companion to tortilla chips, it's also an excellent (and easy) recipe enhancer. Looking to spice 
up a bit of pan-fried fish? A layer of chunky Pico De Gallo will add just the right amount of zest. Making a quick 
Tex-Mex queso? Simply add a tub of Trader Joe's Mild Pico De Gallo to a skillet of melted cheese and milk, and 
you're there, compadre. Scrambled eggs, omelets, breakfast burritos - pretty much any savory breakfast you can 
name could do with a little Pico De Gallo, too.

In addition to being a great convenience, Trader Joe's Mild Pico De Gallo Salsa is also a great value. You'll find 
each 12-ounce tub in our deli section for $2.99 - that's a lot of Pico por un poco.

title: Roasted Garlic Hummus
description:
Trader Joe's and hummus go a long way back. And there's a reason that Trader Joe's Roasted Garlic Hummus 
Dip, in particular, has remained a staple of our refrigerated case for so long - more than 20 years and counting! 
- it's just that good. Creamy in texture, easy to scoop (especially if you're using our Pita Bite Crackers, [sku 
90701]), and loaded with bold, but not overpowering, roasted garlic flavor, it's a delightfully healthy vegetarian 
option for parties, lunches, or any snacking occasion. Of course, if you want to get even more inventive with 
it, try using our Roasted Garlic Hummus as a spread on a sandwich, or stuffed into a pita pocket with your 
favorite salad fixin's for a bit of Mediterranean flair, one spoonful at a time. 

We're selling eight ounce tubs of Trader Joe's Roasted Garlic Hummus Dip for $1.99* each- a price we've held 
since we introduced it way back in the 20th century. Value, thy name is Hummus.

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Roasted Garlic Hummus

title: Aioli Garlic Mustard Sauce
description:
Trader Joe's Aioli Garlic Mustard Sauce takes the very idea of mustard and stands it on its head, throws it for 
a loop, and flies it in the face of expectation. Literally translated to "Garlic" (ai) and "oil" (oli), Aioli is what 
gives this creative condiment its cachet. With a base of not-too-pungent mustard, the mixture of garlic, oil, and 
egg contribute a smooth, mellow, garlicky creaminess that makes this mustard unique among its peers. The 
Mustard flavor shines through, with a garlicky accent that improves everything it touches. 

Dipping sauce for fries? Check. Spread for a burger or hot dog bun? Check. Ingredient in one-of-a-kind salad 
dressings? Check. Dip for veggies? Check. Only 15 calories per serving? Check, please! You'll find nine-ounce 
jars of Trader Joe's Aioli Garlic Mustard Sauce in our grocery aisle every day.

Aioli Garlic Mustard Sauce
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Cheese Board","Cut The Mustard","Pour It On"]

title: Organic Mayonnaise
description:
Who would've thought that when a pandemic hit, among the shortages of toilet paper and pasta, we would also 
see a short supply of mayonnaise! Because people are passionate about their mayonnaise, and because we can't 
provide enough of our Trader Joe's Organic Mayonnaise [sku 60932] at this moment in time, we are choosing to 
make available a comparable substitute in Suzie's Organic Real Mayo.

Like our regular Organic Mayonnaise, Suzie's is a Real Mayo - there's no skimping on flavor or richness here. It's 
made for us using expeller pressed organic soybean oil and organic eggs. It's silky-smooth, ideal for spreading, 
and did we mention it's rich? Oh, yes. Fold it in to chicken or egg salad, slather it on a sandwich, or blend it 
into your favorite dip recipe. 

An added bonus that some of our regular mayo customers may-o may not like better about Suzie's Organic Real 
Mayo is that it comes in a convenient, 12 fluid-ounce, squeezable bottle. Just squeeze, spread, and celebrate!

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Suzie's Real Organic Mayo

title: Calabrian Chili Spicy Pasta Sauce
description:
When it's cold outside, our taste buds turn toward hearty, warming meals to ward off winter's chill. It's better 
still when those hearty meals are bursting with bright, vibrantly flavored ingredients to remind us of the bright, 
vibrant spring days in our not-so-distant future. With that in mind, we're tickled to tout the newest addition to 
our pasta sauce set: Trader Joe's Calabrian Chili Spicy Pasta Sauce!

Our Calabrian Chili Spicy Pasta Sauce offers a pleasant kick of flavor thanks to the Calabrian Chili hot sauce 
emulsified in its classic tomato base. Beautifully balanced with a touch of honey, the Chilis are also responsible 
for the Sauce's striking orange hue. It's an exceptionally thick Sauce that manages to be creamy without the use 
of actual cream, with the power to coat a plethora of pasta shapes with ease. Try tossing it with our Pappardelle 
Pasta [sku 73090] or Spinach Tortellini [sku 95231] and topping with a generous grating of Toscano Cheese 
with Black Pepper [sku 94535] for a quick, cozy, weeknight meal. Or noodle around with non-pasta pairings: it 
makes a dynamite dip for dunking Breaded Mozzarella Cheese Sticks [sku 50209], and adds savory complexity 
when slathered on a Pizza Crust [sku 65225]. 

Calabrian Chili Spicy Pasta Sauce
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Dinner Hack","Mouth On Fire","Pair With Wine"]

title: Garlic Spread Dip
description:
We love to develop flavorful, time-saving products. We also love to invent words and descriptors to categorize 
said products. Since we couldn't definitively declare this mousse-like, garlicky masterpiece a spread or a dip, and 
we didn't want to pigeonhole it into one usage versus another, the solution was simple: we dubbed it Trader Joe's 
Garlic Spread-Dip!

This kicky Garlic Spread-Dip has its origins in Middle Eastern cuisine, where it's called toum (say "toom"), the 
Arabic word for garlic. Fresh garlic cloves, canola oil, salt and lemon juice are slowly blended together to create 
an emulsion, which sounds simple in theory, but is actually a time-and-effort intensive process to ensure the oil 
and lemon juice are properly incorporated. And as anyone who's attempted to make mayonnaise or hollandaise 
sauce from scratch can attest, the finished product doesn't always turn out as intended.  With Trader Joe's Garlic 
Spread-Dip, the hard work is done for you, so you can just open the container, scoop and eat.

The versatility of this Spread-Dip cannot be overstated - simply use it anywhere you desire a creamy, bracing 
kick of garlic flavor. Serve it as a dip with French fries. Baste it on roast chicken or grilled meats. Slather it on 
hamburgers or hot dogs. Feel free to go outside the suggested spread-dip application and add a healthy dollop 
to pasta sauces, soups or salad dressings or extra zing. You'll be happy you did.

You may want to brace your taste buds, but there's no need to brace your wallet. We're selling each eight ounce 
tub of this intensely flavorful Garlic Spread-Dip for a WOW price of $2.99, everyday. 

10.10.
16
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Cheese Board","Gild The Lily","Pair With Wine"]

title: Sweet Cannoli Dip
description:
There's a time-honored saying that "it's what's on the inside that counts", and that's especially true if you happen 
to be talking about a superlatively sweet, cream-filled pastry. Taking this axiom to heart, we've created a dip 
that's entirely inspired by what's on the inside of a classic Italian dessert: introducing Trader Joe's Sweet Cannoli 
Dip! Made with a base of cream cheese, sour cream, and ricotta, every bite of this delectable dessert Dip is 
remarkably rich, with sweet, vanilla-tinged, ever-so-slightly tart notes and a velvety, frosting-like consistency 
 just like what you'd find within a freshly baked cannoli.

Freed from the confines of its traditional, crispy, pastry shell, Trader Joe's Sweet Cannoli Dip can be enjoyed 
in any situation that calls for something extra sweet. Try it as a spread on crackers or short cake, as a layer in a 
super luxurious trifle, or mixed with chopped fresh berries and melon for a full-flavored fruit salad. Of course, 
our favorite way to indulge might be the one most tied to its inspiration: as a dip with crispy, crunchy, Belgian 
Butter Waffle Cookies [sku 67004], to create a kind of deconstructed, shareable cannoli dessert. Meraviglioso!

Sweet Cannoli Dip

title: Organic Roasted Red Pepper and Almond Pesto Sauce
description:
Our Genova Pesto [sku 15759] salutes the very first pesto sauce that has its roots in northern Italy. Like the 
original, our Genova is garlicky, cheesy, and nutty, with a vibrant green hue owed to the fresh basil that's been 
pounded together with oil and other ingredients to create a delectable pasta partner. But the word "pesto" 
really just means "to pound, or crush" (in the Ligurian language of the Middle Ages), which seems to open up 
a world of possibilities. Taking the implicit cue, we've applied this namesake technique to a different group of 
ingredients, calling the final product: Trader Joe's Organic Roasted Red Pepper and Almond Pesto Sauce. 

While there is still some basil in this Pesto, the real star of the show is Organic Roasted Red (Bell) Peppers. 
These are crushed with organic PDO Pecorino Romano cheese, organic almonds, organic onions, organic 
garlic, and a handful of organic herbs and spices, including marjoram, basil, and paprika. These ingredients 
are artfully emulsified with a combination of organic extra virgin olive oil and organic sunflower oil. The final 
flavors are delicately fine-tuned with touches of organic cane sugar, and organic apple cider vinegar.

Although the fiery red-orange color of our Organic Roasted Red Pepper Pesto may look completely different 
from the pesto of the Genoese, the concept and application is very familiar. Simply take spoonfuls of this rich, 
roasted, cheesy, nutty, flavorful Sauce and toss it with your favorite cooked Trader Joe's pasta shape. One taste 
and we think you'll agree-Trader Joe's is totally crushing it in the pesto game!

Organic Roasted Red Pepper 
and Almond Pesto Sauce

title: Truffle Dip
description:
The lush, savory, umami flavors of truffle make it a natural companion to soft, creamy, and cheesy foods. 
Nowhere is that more apparent than in Trader Joe's Truffle Dip, our newest addition to the Trader Joe's truffle-
based culinary canon. Starting with an exceptionally creamy base made from ricotta, parmesan, and cream 
cheese, this Dip then delivers a one-two punch of truffle with the inclusion of both black truffle paste and white 
truffle-infused olive oil. Together, these ingredients create a uniquely flavorful experience that happens to work 
just as well as a sandwich spread or topping for ultra-luxe nachos as it does a traditional dip. 

Speaking of tradition, while you'd traditionally pay top dollar for such extravagance, at Trader Joe's, you'll only 
pay $4.99* for a 7.5 ounce tub of Trader Joe's Truffle Dip. For a limited time, you'll find it in our refrigerated 
case, next to the other dips.

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Truffle Dip

title: Red Pepper, Cranberry & Walnut Dip
description:
The category of "dips" is a deceptively diverse one. There are, of course, savory dips, sweet dips, spicy dips, even 
some refreshingly tart dips. And then, every now and then, you come across something like Trader Joe's Red 
Pepper, Cramberry & Walnut Dip, which manages to contain all of those multitudinous flavors at once. It's 
made with a mix of peppery pimentos, dried cranberries, and chopped walnuts to provide a harmonious mix 
of autumn-inspired tastes and satisfying textures in every single bite. And it's the latest seasonal star to hit the 
shelves of your neighborhood Trader Joe's refrigerator case.

Our Red Pepper, Cranberry & Walnut Dip makes an ideal appetizer for a pre-holiday meal or autumnal 
cocktail party snack table, an apt accessory for all kinds of charcuterie boards, and a splendid spread for savory 
sandwiches-especially one made with some leftover Thanksgiving turkey. Try scooping it with chips or crostini, 
a warm piece of pita or Lavash [sku 26878], or even your favorite raw, crunchy veggies. For some serious seasonal 
synergy, we recommend enjoying it with our Pumpkin Cranberry Crisps [sku 51246]. Fall-icious!

Red Pepper, Cranberry & Walnut Dip

title: Vegan Salmonesque Spread
description:
If you've taken a look at the dips section of our refrigerated case lately, you've likely noticed a distinct proliferation 
of plant-based fare. This uptick in vegan versions of our classic dips and spreads is no mere happenstance-it's 
part of a concerted effort to make more options available to our customers who don't eat dairy or meat. And 
now, we're proud to introduce our first foray into plant-based seafood with Trader Joe's Vegan Salmonesque 
Spread. Made with a base of dairy-free cream cheese, to which our supplier adds savory bits of plant-based 
smoked salmon, chopped dill, and tart, briney capers, each bite of this Spread effortlessly evokes the flavors of 
our classic Smoked Salmon Dip [sku 50232], all without containing any salmon-or any other animal-based 
products, for that matter. It's downright Salmonesque!

Just like the original dip that inspired it, our Salmonesque Spread has a remarkable range of uses. For breakfast, 
it pairs perfectly with a well-toasted Everything Bagel [sku 92267]. At lunch, we like it as a creamy condiment 
for a vegan sandwich. And come dinnertime (or an anytime you're in the mood for a savory, Salmonesque 
snack) it makes an easy appetizer with your favorite crackers or chips.

Vegan Salmonesque Spread
with Capers & Dill
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Brunch All Day","Effortless Entertaining","Feeling Adventurous","Make It Meatless"]

title: Fresh Cranberry Orange Relish
description:
John Lennon sang it all, "Cranberry Sauce." What does it mean? ¿ at all depends on your preference. We 
carry a cadre of quality, natural Cranberry Sauces during the holidays (along with fresh cranberries), so that 
you can puzzle it out on your palate or simply put the one you love on your plate. One o¿ ering, Pilgrim Joe's 
Cranberry Orange Relish, adds a twist of fruity ¿ avor to the traditional sauce you all know and love.

If you prefer a bittersweet bite to a more traditional cranberry sauce, our Cranberry Orange Relish is the 
perfectly zesty, fresh choice. Uncooked, this sauce is made with ¿ nely chopped cranberries and California 
Valencia oranges that are mixed with a bit of pure cane sugar to cut the brilliant bite a bit. ¿ e oranges give this 
traditional accompaniment an untraditional twist-one of our favorite pastimes here at Trader Joe's. And we've 
been carrying it since 1984, so you know we're not just saying that.

"Relishes" are meant for dressing up foods and meals. ¿ is tangy red (no, not orange, as the name might lead 
you to believe) relish does just that. It adds a pop of color and compliments the greens and browns and yellows 
on your holiday plate.

Pucker up! Grab your own 16 ounce container of Pilgrim Joe's Orange Cranberry Relish for just $3.49, around 
just for the holiday season.

title: Pumpkin Chipotle Roasting Sauce
description:
We think it's time to reacquaint yourself with your oven. It's been off all summer, but as temperatures begin to 
cool, our appetites crave the low-and-slow, deeply melded, caramelized flavors that only a good roasting can 
yield. To help kick off roasting season, allow us to introduce Trader Joe's Pumpkin Chipotle Roasting Sauce. 
With its bespeckled, red-orange hue, not only does this Sauce look like fall, but it tastes like fall, too. You'll 
find plenty of creamy, savory Pumpkin flavor, accented with classic warming spices, like cinnamon, ginger, 
nutmeg, allspice, and clove. You'll also note its serious depth and complexity, thanks to tangy apple cider 
vinegar, sweet molasses, and, of course, smoky Chipotle peppers in adobo sauce. 

This stellar Sauce is made for us by the same supplier that makes our Magnificsauce [sku 69916]-so you already 
know just how magnificent their sauce-making skills are. Try coating some Baby Cauliflower [sku 66248] or 
Organic Mini Sweet Peppers [sku 57202] with this seasonal Sauce before roasting them in a hot oven. Use it as a 
marinade for chicken or pork that you can then shred for an aromatic, taco filling. Or add some autumnal flair 
to your next pasta night by adding a touch of cream to the Sauce and tossing with Organic Cascatelli Pasta [sku 
72471]. We're selling each 14.5-ounce jar for $3.49, while we can keep it in stock. Happy roasting!

Pumpkin Chipotle 
Roasting Sauce
tags: ["Cold Front","Dinner Hack","Fall Faves","Pair With Wine","Pour It On"]

title: Organic Artichoke Pasta Sauce
description:
There's a new pasta sauce gracing our grocery shelves, and this one is a piece of art-artichoke, that is. Trader 
Joe's Organic Artichoke Sauce is a thick and creamy Sauce, made with Italian ricotta, Parmigiano Reggiano, 
and tender, chopped Artichokes. Our supplier is located in Puglia, Italy-an area  celebrated for their artichokes. 
And not only is our supplier 100% Organic, they even grow and harvest the artichokes themselves. 

For a weeknight meal masterpiece that comes together in minutes, use our Organic Artichoke Sauce as the 
paint to a blank canvas of your favorite noodles. Simply heat the sauce, add a couple spoonfuls of pasta water, 
then toss in your cooked noodles of choice. The pasta water will help the Sauce coat each and every noodle, so 
each bite has an excellent composition of noodle to sauce. And while this is, first and foremost, a Pasta Sauce, 
consider some other tasty applications-atop a pizza, roasted with veggies, or baked with Shredded Mozzarella 
[sku 81085] and served as a dip. 

Organic Artichoke
Pasta Sauce

title: Gochujang Paste
description:
With origins dating to at least the 1600s, and possibly earlier, gochujang isn't so much an ingredient as it is an 
institution of Korean cuisine unto itself. Traditionally made from a mix of fermented soybeans, rice, barley, 
salt, and, of course, spicy red peppers, gochujang has a thick consistency and a delightfully complex flavor that's 
a rare mix of savory, sweet, and spicy, all at once. In the case of Trader Joe's Gochujang, we reached out to a 
supplier in South Korea who uses traditional fermentation techniques to achieve this uniquely delicious flavor 
profile, resulting in a highly versatile pepper paste that works just as well as a condiment as it does a soup base, 
a marinade, a dipping sauce, and so much more.

Our Gochujang's beautifully balanced elements of sweet and heat make it an excellent choice for flavoring 
proteins of all kinds, from barbecued beef to pan-seared porkloin, crispy fried chicken wings to hearty tofu 
stew. It can spice up burgers when used as a spread, can be enjoyed with french fries either on its own or 
mixed with mayo, and adds a whole new dimension of flavor when added to noodle soups. And for a fun, fiery 
appetizer, it's great for making kimchi-inspired quick pickles with salted smashed cucumbers.

Gochujang

title: Corn and Chile Tomato-less Salsa
description:
Perhaps not as corny as the Fearless Flyer, but Trader Joe's Corn & Chile Salsa is definitely corny. In a good 
way. It's an a-maizing condiment, beginning with a base of sweet corn, and blended with finely diced red bell 
peppers, onions, jalapeño peppers, and a bit of sugar. By "a base of sweet corn," we mean, "lots and lots of sweet 
corn." As in, 1.8 ears of corn in every jar - we have taken them off their cobs to make them fit. (We've sold 
enough of this salsa that over time, this has added up to more than 41,313,173 ears of corn.) It has a little kick, 
but it's not what we'd call hot. 

Pile it into tacos or burritos, scoop it up with Organic Corn Dippers [sku 92482], spoon it over salads or chili or 
soup, use it as a dip for veggies, fold it into scrambled eggs, serve it as a side dish with grilled chicken or fish, 
blend it into Queso Dip [99262], or even use it in place of traditional relish on a hot dog. 

You'll really relish our price of $2.49 for each 13.75 ounce jar. Look for Trader Joe's Corn & Chile Salsa in our 
grocery aisle.

title: Homestyle Salsa Especial Mild
description:
Our Trader Joe's Homestyle Salsa 
Especial Mild has less heat than our 
Medium version, but retains the same 
great flavor profile.  This salsa has a 
smooth texture and a unique herb flavor.  
Serve it with eggs, grilled fish, or 
Mexican cuisine or just eat it by itself 
with chips.  We are selling our Trader 
Joe's Homestyle Salsa Especial Mild in a 
12 ounce container for $2.99.

title: Thai Style Yellow Curry Sauce
description:
Ah, Thai curry, the hearty, comfort food dish of Southeastern Asia. And while we know how capable you are to 
source, bake, and blend all the ingredients needed for a great Thai curry just fine and dandy, Trader Joe's Thai 
Yellow Curry Sauce is looking to take the load off of your shoulders and get lip-smackingly piquant curry in a 
bowl and on your dining table in minutes flat.

Traditional curry colorings used to be as simple as indicating the level of spice ready to be unleashed within 
(ranging from red - hot, yellow - mild, green - subtle zest). But as chefs began whipping more unique flavors 
into their curries, each color became associated with more than just their heat content. In the case of Trader 
Joe's Thai Yellow Curry Sauce, we've honored the modern recipe of a zesty, ginger-forward sauce packed full 
of onion, garlic, red chillies, and of course garlic! All of this is blended together with creamy coconut milk 
making for the rich, velvety sauce we all know and love. With this sauce you can make a traditional yellow 
curry dish in no time! Cook up some meat, poultry, tofu, or veggies until done, stir in our Thai Yellow Curry 
Sauce, simmer until heated through, and serve on a bed of rice.

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

title: Vegan Kale, Cashew & Basil Pesto
description:
In modern cuisine, "pesto" is often used to describe any number of ingredients finely chopped and blended 
together into a sauce or paste. Traditionally, though, pesto is a combination of fresh basil, nuts, garlic, Parmesan 
cheese and oil-and it's delicious. But what about our vegan and dairy-averse friends? Why shouldn't they be 
able to enjoy the creamy, green luxury that is traditional pesto? We think they should, so we've gone and created 
a real deli-section delight: fresh Vegan Kale, Cashew & Basil Pesto. 

Trader Joe's Vegan Kale, Cashew & Basil Pesto is a simple blend of-surprise, surprise-kale, cashew butter, 
and basil, mixed together with olive oil, lemon juice, and water, then seasoned with garlic, salt, and pepper. The 
kale gives the Pesto some serious depth, the basil infuses it with freshness, and the cashew butter lends it enough 
creaminess to leave you saying, "Parmesan? Who needs Parmesan?!" Exaaaactly. 

In addition to being delicious, Trader Joe's Vegan Kale, Cashew & Basil Pesto is also impressively versatile. 
Toss it with your favorite TJ's pasta. Use it as a dip for chips, crackers, and crudités. Spread it on a sandwich or 
in a wrap. Luckily, this Pesto is delicious regardless of your dietary preferences, and omnivores can feel free to 
use Vegan Kale, Cashew & Basil Pesto as a marinade for chicken or a topping for fish.  

The only time we've seen pesto in this format outside of a vegan restaurant, it was going for $9.99 per pound. At 
Trader Joe's, however, we believe in spending a little green to get a lot of green, so we're selling each 8-ounce tub 
of Trader Joe's Vegan Kale, Cashew & Basil Pesto for $3.69. You'll find it in our deli cases. 

10.02.
17

title: Ube Spread
description:
One way to describe ube: a purple-hued yam popular and most often grown in the Philippines. Another way 
to describe ube: a unique flavor (and color!) that has captivated our customers for several years and counting. 
Truth be told, ube is both of these things, and this summer, we're offering yet another sweet way to scratch that 
ube itch: Trader Joe's Ube Spread.

True to its name, our Ube Spread boasts ube purée as its first ingredient, which means it goes big on the 
distinct, craveable, coconut-meets-pistachio Ube flavor. Butter, cream, and coconut cream gives it its smooth, 
buttery texture; cane sugar sweetens the deal; and sea salt brings out even more of the Spread's yummy, yammy 
flavor. Its eye-catching purple hue originates from the ube itself, but we've stepped-up the saturation with a 
splash of purple carrot juice, making it a pretty-in-purple sight for both your peepers and your palate alike!

Spread Ube Spread on toasted TJ's Braided & Sliced Brioche [sku 71239], waffles, or pancakes. Incorporate it 
into baked goods. Spoon it over scoops of ice cream-even TJ's Ube Ice Cream [sku 61854]. There's not much 
ube can't do-be... except stick around forever. If you already know this Ube is for you-be, head to TJ's today!

Ube Spread

title: Truffle Flavored BBQ Sauce
description:
We ask: why does truffle pair so well with such a wide variety of flavors? Is it the fact that its rich, enchanting 
aroma tends to wake up the finer details of a dish? Is it the fact that its unique, intensely umami-forward profile 
gives your taste buds something new to work against a familiar flavor? Or is it just because it's, well, simply 
delicious? The truth is, likely, a mix of all three-or, at the very least, all three are easily evident in Trader 
Joe's Truffle Flavored BBQ Sauce, the newest entry (and dare we say, one of the tastiest yet) into our seasonal 
summer truffle lineup.

Starting with a bold, smoky, classic BBQ base of sugar, tomato, and vinegar, our supplier adds a suite of savory 
seasonings including garlic, oregano, cumin, cinnamon, and, of course, bits of black summer truffle. The 
resulting Sauce is delectably spicy, satisfyingly sweet (but not too sweet), and rich with those ineffably umami 
notes that only truffle can provide. We especially like it served on something savory and juicy, like a rack of ribs 
or a hot-off-the-grill Organic Beef Hot Dog [sku 57562].

Truffle Flavored BBQ Sauce

title: Truffle Aioli
description:
Just in time for grilling season, we're bringing another Truffle-based treat to our shelves in the form of a 
compelling condiment, namely, Trader Joe's Truffle Aioli. 

Umami-rich Truffles are speckled throughout this Aioli (literally translated to "Garlic" (ai) and "oil" (oli)). 
Truffle Aioli delivers a dose of decadence wherever it's spread, offering a powerhouse of flavor for everyone 
to enjoy-and it's emulsified without eggs, making it a vegan-friendly option for your imminent summer 
cookouts, barbecues, and picnics. 

It makes a terrifically creamy dip for Patio Potato Chips [sku 62977] or your favorite veggie crudités. Slather it
